## Migration Impact & Risks

1. **Router Broken References**:
   Updating `auth_service.py` removes `get_current_user` and `get_admin_user`.
   *Mitigation*: We are migrating these to [dependencies.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/dependencies.py) and updating imports in [curriculum.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/routes/curriculum.py).
2. **Transaction Scoping**:
   If we rollback inside the service, the caller might try to commit a closed/failed session.
   *Mitigation*: We will let the exceptions bubble up cleanly, so the router/caller knows the operation failed. Since routers use FastAPI's dependency injection (`get_db`), the database session lifecycle is managed per request, and failed commits are caught at the service layer.
